    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>it's just not that simple. \"professional help\" sounds so clinical and useless when you're literally looking at millions in debt and a ruined reputation. people don't help you fix a destroyed life, they just tell you to breathe while your world burns. there's no \"navigating\" this. it's just a permanent mistake that I have to live with every single second. it feels like the only thing that stops the shame is to just... not be here to feel it anymore. does that even make sense?",
